spec: concurrent_futures_extra178
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor and ThreadPoolExecutor identity — ProcessPoolExecutor.__name__=='ProcessPoolExecutor' (len=19); ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.process'; ProcessPoolExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__=='Executor'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__=='ThreadPoolExecutor' (len=18); ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.thread'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__=='Executor'; Executor.__name__=='Executor' (len=8); Executor.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'."
    - "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.__name__ == 'ProcessPoolExecutor' (len=19: P-r-o-c-e-s-s-P-o-o-l-E-x-e-c-u-t-o-r). ProcessPoolExecutor uses worker processes for CPU-bound tasks, bypassing the GIL. It is defined in concurrent.futures.process and inherits from Executor. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__ == 'ThreadPoolExecutor' (len=18: T-h-r-e-a-d-P-o-o-l-E-x-e-c-u-t-o-r). ThreadPoolExecutor uses worker threads for I/O-bound tasks. It is defined in concurrent.futures.thread and inherits from Executor. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "concurrent.futures.Executor.__name__ == 'Executor' (len=8: E-x-e-c-u-t-o-r). Executor is the abstract base class for both pool executors; its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'. MRO for both pool executors: [Executor, Executor, object] giving __mro__.__len__()==3. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

